		{
			"name": "Example Workflows",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Complete Workflow Example",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"health"
							]
						},
						"description": "# Complete Workflow\n\n1. **Login to Nudge API** (in 'External Auth' folder)\n   - Token is automatically saved to `auth_token` variable\n\n2. **Check Agent Status**\n   - See available tools and configuration\n\n3. **Send Messages**\n   - Create tasks\n   - List tasks\n   - Filter tasks\n   - Update tasks\n   - Delete tasks\n\n4. **Reset Conversation** (optional)\n   - Clear history when needed\n\n## Natural Language Examples\n\n- \"Create a task called 'Team meeting' at 2 PM for 60 minutes\"\n- \"Show me all my tasks\"\n- \"Find all CREATED tasks in the Work category\"\n- \"Mark task <id> as COMPLETED\"\n- \"Delete task <id>\"\n- \"Search for tasks containing 'documentation'\"\n\n## Task Categories\n- ACTION - Active tasks\n- ANCHOR - Fixed schedule items\n- TRANSIT - Travel/commute\n\n## Task Statuses\n- CREATED - New task\n- COMPLETED - Finished\n- FAILED - Could not complete\n- DEFERRED - Postponed\n\n## Time Format\nTime in minutes from midnight:\n- 360 = 6:00 AM\n- 540 = 9:00 AM\n- 720 = 12:00 PM\n- 1080 = 6:00 PM"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Example workflows and documentation for using the AI Agent API."
		}
